      "note_no": "27",
      "note": "Lit., \"the garden\". There is a considerable difference of opinion among the commentators as to what is meant here by \"garden\": a garden in the earthly sense, or the paradise that awaits the righteous in the life to come, or some special garden in the heavenly regions? According to some of the earliest commentators (see Manar I, 277), an earthly abode is here alluded to - namely, an environment of perfect ease, happiness and innocence. In any case, this story of Adam is obviously one of the allegories referred to in 3:7."
